        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "generation of the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts atmospheric 28 reanalysis (ERA5). 2 The modeling domain is centered at 34.533\u00b0 N and 108.917\u00b0 E and 29 covers the entire mainland China. It contains 35 vertical levels with the top level at 50 hPa. 30 The model time step is 180 s. The physics options of the WRF configuration include the 31 Yonsei University scheme 3 for planetary boundary layer dynamics, the Noah scheme 4 for land 32 surface model, the Rapid Radiative Transfer Model scheme 5 for longwave radiation, the 33 Dudhia scheme 6 for shortwave radiation, a revised version of Kain-Fritsch scheme 7 for 34 cumulus parameterization, and the Lin et al. scheme 8 for cloud microphysics. The ERA5 data 35 are used as initial and boundary conditions and the meteorological nudging field in the WRF 36 simulation. Grid nudging is applied to temperature, horizontal winds, and geopotential heights, 37 with a nudging coefficient of 3\u00d710 -4 s -1 for all the variables. Horizontal winds are nudged in 38 all vertical layers. Other variables are nudged only in the layers above the planetary boundary 39 layer. The nudging is conducted every 3 hours. WRF is restarted every six days with the first 40 12 hours for spinning up. The generated meteorological fields are then processed by the 41 Meteorology-Chemistry Interface Processor (MCIP) 9 so that the outputs can be used directly 42 to drive the air quality model, i.e., the Community Multiscale Air Quality (CMAQ",
            "latex": null,
            "type": "figure"
        },
